ding="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig10c.jpeg" height="1800" width="1394" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig10c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig10d.jpeg" height="1075" width="929" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig10d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig11a.jpeg" height="1454" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig11b.jpeg" height="1272" width="1530" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig12.jpeg" height="493" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig12" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12</span> Collagenous colitis. Diagram shows the etiopathogenesis and natural history of microscopic colitis. <i>CC</i> = collagenous colitis, <i>GIT</i> = gastrointestinal tract, <i>LC</i> = lymphocytic colitis, <i>MC</i> = microscopic colitis, <i>SSRI</i> = selective seratonin reuptake inhibitor.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig12">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig13a.jpeg" height="853" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig13a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig13b.jpeg" height="854" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig13b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig14a.jpeg" height="1596" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig14a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig14b.jpeg" height="1476" width="1659" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig14b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig15a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1794" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig15a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig15b.jpeg" height="1800" width="1762" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig15b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig16" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig16.jpeg" height="477" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig16" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 16</span> Diagram shows the etiopathogenesis and natural history of inflammatory bowel disease. <i>IBD</i> = inflammatory bowel disease, <i>IFN</i> = interferon, <i>IL</i> = interleukin, <i>UC</i> = ulcerative colitis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig16">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig17" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig17.jpeg" height="855" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig17" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 17</span> Crohn disease. Photomicrograph (original magnification, ×2; H-E stain) of a small-bowel biopsy specimen shows a mucosal ulcer (arrowhead), acute inflammatory infiltration of the lamina propria, thickening of the muscularis propria, crypt distortion, and crypt abscess (arrows), findings indicative of Crohn disease.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig17">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig18" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig18.jpeg" height="735" width="1024" aria-labelledby="fig18" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18</span> Ulcerative colitis. Photomicrograph (original magnification, ×8; H-E stain) of a colonic biopsy specimen shows acute inflammatory infiltrates, a loss of glands, cryptitis, and crypt distortion with no transmural involvement, findings indicative of ulcerative colitis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig18">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig19a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1729" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig19a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig19b.jpeg" height="1422" width="1258" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig19b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig19c.jpeg" height="1800" width="1499" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig19c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig19d.jpeg" height="1800" width="1609" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig19d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19e" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig19e.jpeg" height="1240" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19e</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig19e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig20" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig20.jpeg" height="1800" width="1646" aria-labelledby="fig20" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20</span> Ulcerative colitis in a 52-year-old man. Coronal contrast-enhanced T1-weighted MR image obtained at the level of the abdomen shows multiple polypoidal lesions (arrow) along the ascending colon and the proximal transverse colon, findings indicative of pseudopolyposis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig20">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig21a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig21a.jpeg" height="1602" width="1430" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 21a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig21a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig21b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig21b.jpeg" height="1566" width="1409" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 21b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig21b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig22a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig22a.jpeg" height="1406" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 22a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig22a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig22b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig22b.jpeg" height="1401" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 22b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig22b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig23" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig23.jpeg" height="1286" width="1656" aria-labelledby="fig23" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 23</span> Gastric involvement in a patient with autoimmune pancreatitis and IgG4 sclerosing disease. Axial contrast-enhanced CT image shows mural thickening of the antropyloric region of the stomach (arrow). Endo-scopic biopsy of the antrum was performed, and increased numbers of IgG4-positive plasma cells were seen, a finding consistent with gastric involvement.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig23">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig24a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig24a.jpeg" height="1196" width="1494" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 24a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig24a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig24b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig24b.jpeg" height="1338" width="1674" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 24b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig24b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig25" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.306105520/asset/images/105520fig25.jpeg" height="831" width="1152" aria-labelledby="fig25" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 25</span> Photomicrograph (original magnification, ×20; H-E stain) of a pancreatic biopsy specimen shows increased numbers of plasma cells and lymphocytes (arrow), a finding indicative of autoimmune pancreatitis with IgG4 sclerosing disease.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.306105520&amp;id=fig25">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Pickard KM, Bremner AR, Gordon JN, MacDonald TT. Microbial-gut interactions in health and disease: immune responses. <em>Best Pract Res Clin Gastroenterol</em> 2004;18(2):271–285.</div><div c